Storage backends are template classes that require a concrete TData type to instantiate. This creates several testing challenges:

Can’t compile templates in isolation - OwningRaggedStorage&lt;TData&gt; needs a TData
Real types are complex - Mask2D has move semantics, large data, etc.
Failure attribution - If a test fails, is it the storage or the data type?
Test organization - Where do storage tests live if they depend on types?




